    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Presidents Special Assistant</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d222fn1">The omitted
                            paragraphs of this memorandum refer to the problem of St. Pierre and
                            Miquelon; see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_140">p.
                                140</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-29">December 29,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Joint Declaration</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Attached are two memoranda from Eden to Halifax relative to the Free French and
                    the listing of the various countries.<note n="2" xml:id="d222fn2">The
                        “memoranda” under reference are the two telegrams from Eden to Halifax, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>The Prime Minister, in his talk with me late this afternoon, suggested the
                    elimination of Section E of the Declaration on the ground that it was
                        repetitious.<note n="3" xml:id="d222fn3">The “Section E” is not identified
                        and no other reference has been found that would indicate its identity. The
                        reference may be to the phrase “and to continue war against,” which appears
                        in paragraph numbered (2) of the draft. This phrase was dropped in the
                        process of incorporating the Russian amendments; see <hi rend="italic"
                            >post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_375">p. 375</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H.L.H.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
